  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he cometh the third time,.... After he had prayed a third time, to the same purport as before: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and saith unto them, sleep on now, and take your rest; which words are spoken ironically: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "it is enough; or \"the end is come\"; as the Syriac and Arabic versions render it, of watching and praying: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the hour is come, behold the son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners; both Jews and Gentiles, by one of his own disciples; See Gill on Matthew 26:45. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "the hour is come, behold the son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners; both Jews and Gentiles, by one of his own disciples; See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 26:45",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
